          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search            Álvaro Martins Homem      3rd Captain-Donatário of Praia   In office 1520–1540   Monarch   Manuel I John III     Preceded by Antão Martins Homem   Succeeded by Antão Martins da Câmara   Constituency Praia   Personal details   Born Álvaro Martins Homem 1535   Citizenship Kingdom of Portugal   Nationality Portuguese   Spouse(s) Beatriz de Noronha   Religion Roman Catholic   Alvaro Martins Homem (born 1535) was a Portuguese nobleman, 3rd Donatary-Captain of Praia da Vitória.[1] Biography[edit] His parents were Antão Martins Homem and Isabel de Ornelas da Câmara. In 1519, Álvaro was married to Beatriz de Noronha,[2] daughter of João de Noronha (descendant of Alfonso Enríquez and Inês de Abreu (daughter of João Fernandes de Andrade and Beatriz Gomes de Abreu).[3] Álvaro Martins Homem is the grandson of Álvaro Martins 1st Captain of Praia.[4] References[edit]   ^ Obras completas: Corsário das Ilhas. Vitorino Nemésio, Fátima Freitas Morna.  ^ Arquivo da Universidade de Lisboa. Universidade de Lisboa.  ^ The Portuguese Columbus: Secret Agent of King John II. Mascarenhas Barreto.  ^ A History of the Azores Islands - Volumen5. James H. Guill.        This article about a Portuguese politician is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e         This biographical article of a European noble is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e         This biographical article related to the military of Portugal is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Álvaro_Martins_Homem_III&oldid=684065586"          Categories: 15th-century Portuguese people16th-century Portuguese peoplePortuguese Roman CatholicsDonatary-Captains of the AzoresPeople from the AzoresPortuguese politician stubsEuropean nobility stubsEuropean military personnel stubsPortugu